### Output Modes

The skill supports three output depths. Default to **Standard** unless
the user specifies otherwise or the context strongly signals a different mode.

| Mode | When to Use | What's Included | Token Cost |
|------|------------|-----------------|------------|
| **âڑ، Quick** | User says "quick scan" / "ه؟«é€ںçœ‹ن¸€ن¸‹" / "just the highlights"; single function; < 50 lines of code | Phase 1 (compact budget) + Phase 2 (top 3 nodes only) + Phase 3 (compact persona, BEFORE only) + 1 dimension (auto-pick most relevant) + top 3 fixes | ~500 words |
| **ًں“‹ Standard** (default) | Normal review request; single file; PR diff | All 3 phases + 2-3 dimensions (auto-select) + full fix table | ~2000 words |
| **ًں”¬ Deep** | User says "و·±ه؛¦هˆ†و‍گ" / "thorough" / "exhaustive"; critical path code; production incident investigation | All 3 phases + ALL 5 dimensions + fix simulation + optimized code snippets + regression risk assessment | ~5000 words |

**Mode detection:** Check user's language for intensity signals.
- "quick" / "ه؟«é€ں" / "ه¤§و¦‚" / "ç®€هچ•çœ‹ن¸‹" â†’ Quick
- "deep" / "و·±ه؛¦" / "thorough" / "exhaustive" / "ه…¨é‌¢" / "è¯¦ç»†" â†’ Deep
- Everything else â†’ Standard

**Override:** Always respect explicit mode requests. If unsure, use Standard.

### Micro-Diagnosis Mode
User can explicitly select which dimensions to run: "هڈھو£€وں¥ه¹¶هڈ‘" / "only check security" / "just the causal graph." Skip unselected dimensions entirely.

### CI Integration
When triggered in a CI context: auto-select Quick mode, fail the pipeline if any ًں”´ P0 finding, warn on ًںں، P1. Output compact format suitable for PR comments.

### Multi-Agent Parallelism
For Deep mode on large files: dispatch Phase 1, different dimensions, and the Meta-Cognitive analysis to parallel agents. Merge results before final output.

### Pipeline Checkpoints

ًں”´ **CHECKPOINT: After Phase 1 â€” verify budget before proceeding.**
- Is the budget total reasonable for the context?
- Are FIXED vs ELASTIC layers correctly labeled?
- If no user goal was given, did you state which default you used?
- **If budget is missing or incomplete â†’ STOP. Fix it. Do not proceed to Phase 2.**

ًں”´ **CHECKPOINT: After Phase 2 â€” verify causal graph + vulnerabilities + attack chain.**
- ًں”‘ KEY BOTTLENECK labeled? (1-node OK if Clean Bill)
- Leverage scores computed?
- Vulnerability scan completed? (8-type + crypto + obfuscation)
- If â‰¥2 vulnerabilities found: ًں”— Attack Chain constructed?
- **If graph missing or vulnerability scan skipped â†’ STOP. Build it.**

ًں”´ **CHECKPOINT: After Phase 3 â€” verify persona before finalizing.**
- Does the persona have a name, mission, and budget?
- BEFORE journey present? (all modes). AFTER journey: one-line projection (Quick) / full section (Standard/Deep)?
- Is there a health score?
- **If persona is generic or missing â†’ STOP. Create a specific persona.**

ًں”´ **CHECKPOINT: Before output â€” verify dimension coverage.**
- At least 1 dimension applied (Quick mode) / 2-3 (Standard) / 5 (Deep)?
- **If dimension count is below mode requirement â†’ STOP. Add missing dimensions.**

