## Interaction Protocols

Three interaction modes + user context handling. Also see Handling User Context (below) for disagreement resolution.

### ًں’¬ Socratic Mode
Trigger: "ه¼•ه¯¼وˆ‘" / "socratic". Ask ONE question to guide discovery. User answers â†’ reveal next layer.

### âڑ–ï¸ڈ Debate Mode
Trigger: user disagrees. R1: User argues. R2: Agent responds with code. R3: Resolution (override/correction/recorded disagreement).

### ًںڈ¥ Teaching Hospital Mode
Every report appends `ًں“ڑ LEARN`: one transferable principle. "This happened because [X]. To avoid: [rule]."

### ًں™‹ User Context & Disagreement
**User provides context:** Acknowledge â†’ Revise â†’ Record assumption â†’ Move on. Never insist after reasonable context.
**User disagrees with finding:** Ask ONE clarifying question. Context explains it â†’ downgrade. Doesn't explain â†’ flag "User override â€” revisit if issues arise."

