## Advanced Diagnostic Dimensions

> **Full reference: `references/dimensions.md`** â€” dimension algorithms, report templates, Vulnerability Detection table, Comment Audit, Self-Praise Scan, Zombie Paths.

**Quick pick:** Ghost Load + Blast Radius are almost always applicable. Minimum: 1 (Quick) / 2-3 (Standard) / 5 (Deep). When stuck, apply MVD â€” each dimension can be minimally applied in 30 seconds. See dimensions.md.
concepts that have no equivalent in traditional performance tooling.
Each is applied automatically â€” the agent decides which dimensions
are relevant based on the code being analyzed.

**Dimension Selection Guide:**

| Dimension | ALWAYS Apply? | Strong Signal (must apply) | Weak/No Signal (may skip) |
|-----------|:--:|----------------------------|---------------------------|
| âڈ³ Debt Interest | No | Any problem that scales with data/users; growth-dependent code paths | All problems are static (fixed-size input, no data growth) |
| ًں‘» Ghost Load | **Almost always** | Any data fetching (SQL, API calls, file I/O) | Pure computation file with no data sources |
| ًں’£ Blast Radius | **Almost always** | Any function called by â‰¥2 consumers; shared utility code | Single-consumer leaf functions with no callers |
| ًں•³ï¸ڈ Time Leak | No | Caches without eviction, event listeners, unbounded buffers, connection pools | Stateless pure functions; short-lived scripts/CLI tools |
| ًں“گ Entropy | No | Code with â‰¥2 distinct code paths (cache hit/miss, small/large input, success/error) | Single-path code with no branching; deterministic I/O |

**Minimum bar:** At least 2 dimensions apply to virtually any non-trivial code.
**Minimum Viable Dimension (MVD) â€” there is no "genuinely stuck":**

| Dimension | Minimum Application (always possible) |
|-----------|--------------------------------------|
| ًں‘» Ghost Load | List every data source. For each: fields fetched vs fields demonstrably used. Even "all used" IS the analysis. |
| ًں’£ Blast Radius | Count callers. Even "one caller, one feature, no revenue impact" (BR=25) IS the analysis. |
| âڈ³ Debt Interest | For each problem: state whether it scales with data/users or is static. Even "static, no growth driver" IS the analysis. |
| ًں•³ï¸ڈ Time Leak | Check for caches/queues/buffers/listeners. Even "none found" IS the analysis. |
| ًں“گ Entropy | Count distinct code paths. Even "one path, H=0, STABLE" IS the analysis. |

**There is no "genuinely stuck" â€” only "haven't applied the minimum analysis yet." Each dimension's MVD takes 30 seconds. If a dimension truly has no signal, state that explicitly with evidence, then skip it.**

