### Dimension 6: âڑ”ï¸ڈ Immune System Analysis

**Concept:** Beyond finding vulnerabilities, assess what defenses ARE present.
Like an immune system audit â€” not "what diseases can you catch" but "how strong is your immune response."

**Checklist:** Circuit breaker آ· Graceful degradation آ· Retry with exponential backoff آ· Input validation layers آ· Feature flag kill switch آ· Rate limiting آ· Timeout on all external calls آ· Fallback/default on failure

Report: `âڑ”ï¸ڈ IMMUNE SYSTEM: [N]/8 defenses present. Weakest gap: [missing defense]. Impact if exploited: [scenario].`

### Dimension 7: ًں—؛ï¸ڈ Trust Boundary Crossing Map

**Concept:** Security engineering maps trust boundaries. Trace every crossing of data from untrusted â†’ trusted zones. At each crossing: validation? sanitization? type checking?

Report: `ًں—؛ï¸ڈ TRUST BOUNDARY: [path]. ًں”´ Unguarded at [location]: [data] enters trusted zone without [check].`

### Dimension 8: ًںڈ° Authentication Flow Integrity

**Concept:** Audit the entire auth flow: Loginâ†’Sessionâ†’Verifyâ†’Authorizeâ†’Destroy. Any gap = bypass.

**Checklist:** Login (no default credentials?) آ· Session creation (HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite?) آ· Session verify (every endpoint?) آ· Authorization (every operation?) آ· Session destroy (on logout/timeout?) آ· Hardcoded tokens? آ· Auth bypass paths?

Report: `ًںڈ° AUTH FLOW: [N]/7 checks passed. Gaps: [list]. Most critical: [gap].`

### Dimension 9: ًں›،ï¸ڈ Defense-in-Depth Gap Analysis

**Concept:** Rate each of 7 defense layers. Absent / Partial / Complete.

**Layers:** Input Validation â†’ Authentication â†’ Authorization â†’ Encryption â†’ Audit Logging â†’ Rate Limiting â†’ Output Encoding

Report: `ًں›،ï¸ڈ DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH: [N]/7 layers complete. Gaps: [list]. Weakest layer: [X] â€” prioritize here.`

### Dimension 10: ًں”Œ Supply Chain Attack Surface

**Concept:** Third-party dependencies are the #1 attack vector. Assess dependency risk.

**Checks:** Direct+transitive dep count آ· Known CVE versions آ· Unmaintained deps آ· Fuzzy version ranges (^, ~, *) آ· GitHub URL installs آ· Over-broad permission requests

Report: `ًں”Œ SUPPLY CHAIN: [N] deps. [X] known CVEs. [Y] unmaintained. Risk: [HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW].`

