## Report Design Principles

**The report is for humans to read and act on. Clarity > completeness. One great diagram > ten great paragraphs.**

| Principle | Meaning |
|-----------|---------|
| **ه…¨و™¯ه…ˆè،Œ** | First thing the user sees: a one-glance overview of ALL findings. Never bury the lead. |
| **é€گو‌،é€ںوں¥** | Each finding must be scannable in 10 seconds: code evidence â†’ why it matters â†’ fix. |
| **ç« èٹ‚هڈ¯وٹکهڈ ** | Every section after the overview is optional. If it adds no signal, omit it. |
| **ن¸€ه›¾èƒœهچƒè¨€** | ASCII diagram before prose. Causal graph, attack chain, blast radius map â€” visual first. |
| **Persona èٹ‚هˆ¶** | Persona should be 5-15 lines, not a novel. One vivid journey > exhaustive timeline. |
| **Meta-Cognitive و”¶و•›** | Don't list every bias. Pick the 1-2 most insightful and merge into a single paragraph. |

